# ==============================================================================
# Browserslist Configuration File (.browserslistrc)
# ==============================================================================
#
# WHAT IS THIS FILE?
# Browserslist is a standard tool used in frontend development to share target
# browser configurations across different build, lint, and optimization tools.
#
# This file is automatically detected and used by tools such as:
#   - Webhint / HTML Hint (compatibility checks for tags like 'theme-color')
#   - Autoprefixer (adds vendor prefixes to CSS automatically)
#   - Babel / SWC (transpiles modern JS into backward-compatible versions)
#   - ESLint-plugin-compat (warns you if you use a JS API unsupported by your targets)
#   - PostCSS & Stylelint (styles compilation and linting)
#
# WHY DO WE USE IT?
# By declaring our target browsers here, linters and compilers know exactly which
# browsers we support. This prevents false-positive warnings (like theme-color
# compatibility messages) while keeping build outputs lean (preventing unnecessary
# polyfills/prefixes for extremely outdated browsers).
#
# QUERY BREAKDOWN:
#   - "> 0.5%": Target browser versions that have global usage statistics
#     greater than 0.5%.
#   - "last 2 versions": Include the last two releases of all major browsers
#     (Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge, Opera, iOS Safari, Android Chrome, etc.).
#   - "Firefox ESR": Include Firefox Extended Support Release (commonly used
#     in corporate, enterprise, and educational environments).
#   - "not dead": Exclude "dead" browsers that no longer receive official
#     security or feature updates (such as Internet Explorer).
#
# WHERE TO GET MORE INFO & TOOLS:
#   - Official Repository & Syntax Guide:
#     https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist
#
#   - Browserslist Playground (Visualizes exactly which browsers your query targets):
#     https://browsersl.ist
#
#   - Browser Feature & Compatibility Database:
#     https://caniuse.com
# ==============================================================================

